explanation: This solution uses a greedy approach to find the smallest positive integer n that is divisible by k and only contains the digit 1. It starts with n = 1 and keeps appending 1 to n until it finds a number that is divisible by k. The time complexity is O(log(k)) because the number of digits in n grows logarithmically with k.

